{
  "stem": "15017.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was making money and doing very, very well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, well, I was working at all the number-one places in England, all the number-one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And you see, they have a thing in all the number-one hotels.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From all over the world, they exchange waiters, musicians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because it is known that if you work there, you're a person that they don't have to worry about.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anyhow, as I was working at the Cafe Anglais in London in Leicester Square, Geraldo-- who was one of the big booking bandleaders at that time-- got the contract with Cunard to supply music.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Queen Mary, at that time, was being refitted from being a trooper and was repainted and refitted and everything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I got the job on the ship, first, as a musician in the band, then later as a bandleader on the Queen Mary.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we, we arrived in-- we-- they, they brought us in July, and we did a shakedown cruise in the, the North Sea.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We then sailed from England.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I arrived in New York on August the 5th, 1947.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Whilst the ship was going and coming in the Hudson, we were met by these fire floats and everybody, and sight-seeing and everybody.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The newly painted Queen Mary was coming in, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was dressed in a suit that was 22 ounces to the pound, you know, of material, you know, with a stiff collar-- very, very British.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "When the ship stopped, I thought I was going to die.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was like I was in an oven.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because it was 93 degrees and the-- what do you-- the humidity was 90.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My cousin was waiting for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
